<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  the members of prime that you guys are pointing the finger at have shown us nothing but the trustworthy side of themselves, and we would like to think the best of people until they prove otherwise to us themselves...until then this matter is closed  - Alianlia <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
People are multi-faceted.  Just because you see one side of a person doesn't mean they behave that way all the time.  Many people put on a visage when in different situations.  Some are calm and collected and think out before they make an action, others jump straight into the flames and/or namecalling.  The point is, even though you see a &quot;trustworthy&quot; side of a member in your guild doesn't mean they are going to put that side forward all the time.<br>
<br>
